<p>murderous &amp; merciless thing it is the French undoubtedly think the Australians are marvels, what a name our glorious land has it is spoken of over here as a sort of mysterious place &amp; anything is likely to spring from it.  As we pass through their villages the French people all come out &amp; have a peep at us, I expect they think we are a rum lot by the way we stroll along for you could scarcely call it a march, for the boys march anyhow, they please themselves.</p>
